<body>

  <h1>European Golden Shoe</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What is the Golden Shoe?</h2>
    <p>
      The European Golden Shoe is an annual football award presented to the top goalscorer in league matches from the 
      top division of every European national league. Originally called the <em>Soulier d'Or</em>, the award was 
      introduced in 1968 and is currently awarded based on a points system reflecting the difficulty of each league.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>📌Key Facts</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>📅Inception:</strong> 1968</li>
      <li><strong>👤Presented By:</strong> European Sports Media (ESM)</li>
      <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Players in top-tier European leagues</li>
      <li><strong>🗳️Scoring System:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>2 points per goal in top 5 leagues (e.g., Premier League, La Liga)</li>
          <li>1.5 points per goal in mid-ranked leagues</li>
          <li>1 point per goal in lower-ranked leagues</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>🥇Notable Winners</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Lionel Messi</strong> – Record 6-time winner with FC Barcelona</li>
      <li><strong>Cristiano Ronaldo </strong> – 4-time winner across different leagues</li>
      <li><strong>Erling Haaland </strong> – 2022–23 winner with Manchester City</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section fun-fact">
    <strong>Fun Fact:</strong> Only league goals count toward the Golden Shoe — not goals in cups or international matches!
  </div>

